1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:04,963
[brazen music playing]

2
00:00:12,137 --> 00:00:14,556
[electronic blipping]

3
00:00:17,809 --> 00:00:19,477
[Marcus] <i>I have something else</i>
<i>for you to do.</i>

4
00:00:19,561 --> 00:00:20,895
<i>How are your driving skills?</i>

5
00:00:20,979 --> 00:00:23,898
[Karla] <i>I can't do Tokyo Drift,</i>
<i>but I'm okay.</i>

6
00:00:23,982 --> 00:00:26,276
[Karla] <i>Buenas noches, señor.</i>

7
00:00:26,359 --> 00:00:30,030
[Marcus] <i>Remember my name.</i>
<i>Chipper Arenas. Okay, Carlotta?</i>

8
00:00:30,613 --> 00:00:32,741
[Lorna] <i>We have a great fight tonight.</i>

9
00:00:32,824 --> 00:00:34,743
I'm sure you'll enjoy it, sir.

10
00:00:35,326 --> 00:00:37,620
[in English] Please. Enjoy, sir.

11
00:00:38,371 --> 00:00:40,373
[in English] I cannot wait
to get my hands on Ame.

12
00:00:40,457 --> 00:00:42,459
[Red, in English] I made arrangements
already. You're gonna have her.

13
00:00:42,542 --> 00:00:44,544
- [Red] <i>Let's enjoy the fight first.</i>
- [Vladimir] <i>Okay.</i>

14
00:00:44,627 --> 00:00:47,297
[Bebang] <i>She has no more fights.</i>
<i>Her last fight was last night.</i>

15
00:00:47,380 --> 00:00:49,257
Why? Did something happen to her?

16
00:00:49,340 --> 00:00:52,510
[Marcus] <i>Maybe I could</i>
<i>take a picture with her?</i>

17
00:00:52,594 --> 00:00:54,512
[Gavin] <i>You're the one we played</i>
<i>basketball with, right?</i>

18
00:00:55,096 --> 00:00:56,139
- Oh!
- Ouch, ouch, ouch!

19
00:00:56,222 --> 00:00:57,140
That was me!

20
00:00:57,223 --> 00:00:59,100
[Vladimir, in English] <i>How about</i>
<i>we try something different?</i>

21
00:00:59,184 --> 00:01:00,185
[Red, in English] <i>What are you thinking?</i>

22
00:01:00,268 --> 00:01:02,353
What is this? Why are they allowing this?

23
00:01:02,437 --> 00:01:05,231
They know they're at
a huge disadvantage in that fight!

24
00:01:05,315 --> 00:01:08,401
[groans and grunts]

25
00:01:08,902 --> 00:01:10,028
[Vladimir chuckles]

26
00:01:10,528 --> 00:01:12,155
[Bebang] <i>Boss…</i>

27
00:01:12,238 --> 00:01:13,615
[Ame] <i>What do you want?</i>

28
00:01:13,698 --> 00:01:15,992
I'm here to save you.

29
00:01:16,076 --> 00:01:17,452
‪PREVIOUSLY

30
00:01:19,579 --> 00:01:22,832
[brazen music continues]

31
00:01:24,626 --> 00:01:26,419
- [inquisitive music playing]
- Fight back.

32
00:01:26,503 --> 00:01:27,754
Fight back!

33
00:01:27,837 --> 00:01:29,214
Quick!

34
00:01:29,297 --> 00:01:30,924
Give me a best actress performance.

35
00:01:31,007 --> 00:01:32,509
Fight back, fight back.

36
00:01:32,592 --> 00:01:33,593
- Ah, uh…
- Fight back.

37
00:01:33,676 --> 00:01:35,678
- [moaning]
- [Marcus mutters]

38
00:01:37,430 --> 00:01:40,517
Where did you come from?
Where's the exit here, huh?

39
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:44,896
[stammers] There's… There's none.

40
00:01:44,979 --> 00:01:47,524
Uh, there's a hallway…

41
00:01:48,566 --> 00:01:51,694
going to the dugout.

42
00:01:53,113 --> 00:01:54,155
There's…

43
00:01:54,989 --> 00:01:57,283
There's a way going to the kitchen.

44
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:01,287
‪[Ame breathes nervously]

45
00:02:03,540 --> 00:02:06,000
There was a bouncer smoking earlier.

46
00:02:06,793 --> 00:02:09,170
Smoking isn't allowed on the floor,

47
00:02:09,254 --> 00:02:10,213
so probably…

48
00:02:11,756 --> 00:02:13,258
Probably he passed through there.

49
00:02:13,341 --> 00:02:15,301
Eh… I don't know.

50
00:02:16,386 --> 00:02:18,471
There's a back entrance here.

51
00:02:18,555 --> 00:02:19,681
We'll go through there.

52
00:02:21,599 --> 00:02:24,185
Ibyang… How's Ibyang?

53
00:02:25,103 --> 00:02:26,104
Playful.

54
00:02:26,896 --> 00:02:27,897
Noisy.

55
00:02:27,981 --> 00:02:29,274
You know her.

56
00:02:30,108 --> 00:02:33,069
How many guards are at the area
where they usually take you?

57
00:02:34,237 --> 00:02:36,656
Ah… Three.

58
00:02:36,739 --> 00:02:38,408
Sometimes two.

59
00:02:39,659 --> 00:02:40,743
Brother…

60
00:02:40,827 --> 00:02:44,372
I really need to leave tonight.

61
00:02:44,873 --> 00:02:47,333
And not just me.

62
00:02:47,834 --> 00:02:48,877
‪[breathing nervously]

63
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:51,170
You need to save them too.

64
00:02:52,672 --> 00:02:55,091
There are many of us locked up here.

65
00:02:55,717 --> 00:02:56,676
All of us…

66
00:02:56,759 --> 00:03:00,305
All of us are victims
of the syndicate running this place.

67
00:03:02,348 --> 00:03:05,685
[suave music playing]

68
00:03:05,768 --> 00:03:08,563
[machine whirring, scraping, snipping]

69
00:03:10,231 --> 00:03:11,065
‪[machine whirring]

70
00:03:12,150 --> 00:03:12,984
‪[machine whirring]

71
00:03:13,568 --> 00:03:14,402
‪[gun cocks]

72
00:03:19,240 --> 00:03:20,074
‪[slow snipping]

73
00:03:29,042 --> 00:03:30,501
[Vladimir, in English] Get up.

74
00:03:30,585 --> 00:03:32,670
[in English] Come, lad.
I'm not done with you yet.

75
00:03:36,925 --> 00:03:39,969
[tense music playing]

76
00:03:40,053 --> 00:03:44,140
[crowd cheering]

77
00:03:44,224 --> 00:03:45,600
[laughs]

78
00:03:45,683 --> 00:03:47,518
Whoo!

79
00:03:47,602 --> 00:03:50,355
[cheering and applauding]

80
00:03:52,023 --> 00:03:53,066
Psst, hey--

81
00:03:55,193 --> 00:03:57,195
- [growls]
- [crowd cheering]

82
00:03:57,278 --> 00:03:58,363
Woo-hoo!

83
00:03:58,947 --> 00:04:00,949
[in English] Yes, sir!

84
00:04:01,532 --> 00:04:03,868
[in English] Whoo! Red, you want a piece?

85
00:04:03,952 --> 00:04:05,828
- [in English] Yes, I'll do it.
- [in English] Let's go!

86
00:04:05,912 --> 00:04:08,289
[grunting]

87
00:04:10,625 --> 00:04:13,461
[crowd cheering and applauding]

88
00:04:13,544 --> 00:04:15,255
[Red] Whoo!

89
00:04:15,338 --> 00:04:16,547
[chuckles]

90
00:04:16,631 --> 00:04:17,966
[Ame] Sir!

91
00:04:18,049 --> 00:04:19,217
Sir, don't!

92
00:04:19,300 --> 00:04:20,843
He won't survive that fall!

93
00:04:20,927 --> 00:04:22,262
Sir, don't, please!

94
00:04:22,345 --> 00:04:23,972
Sir!

95
00:04:24,055 --> 00:04:25,265
- [clacks and shatters]
- [crowd gasps]

96
00:04:25,348 --> 00:04:26,474
Darryl!

97
00:04:26,557 --> 00:04:27,684
[both] Whoo!

98
00:04:28,810 --> 00:04:30,520
- [Red] Whoo!
- [Vladimir] Yes! [laughs]

99
00:04:33,022 --> 00:04:35,149
Darryl! Darryl!

100
00:04:35,233 --> 00:04:36,818
Darryl! Darryl!

101
00:04:37,402 --> 00:04:38,486
Darryl!

102
00:04:38,569 --> 00:04:41,656
[gasping for breath] Forgive me, Ame.

103
00:04:42,615 --> 00:04:45,618
Looks like I can't…

104
00:04:46,661 --> 00:04:48,079
help you escape.

105
00:04:48,162 --> 00:04:50,915
No, no, don't say that. We can still
get out of here, okay?

106
00:04:50,999 --> 00:04:53,001
We can still get out of here!

107
00:04:53,084 --> 00:04:57,088
- [uneasy music playing]
- [groans, gasping for air]

108
00:04:57,797 --> 00:05:00,800
We need to bring him to the hospital!

109
00:05:01,467 --> 00:05:02,927
- Darryl!
- [grunting, gasping]

110
00:05:03,011 --> 00:05:04,470
Darryl!

111
00:05:05,263 --> 00:05:06,764
Darryl! Darryl!

112
00:05:06,848 --> 00:05:08,766
- Darryl!
- [grunting]

113
00:05:10,977 --> 00:05:14,856
[man grunts]

114
00:05:29,454 --> 00:05:31,414
What are you doing here?

115
00:05:31,497 --> 00:05:32,999
You have so much time.

116
00:05:34,584 --> 00:05:36,461
Why? What's your problem?

117
00:05:36,544 --> 00:05:38,212
At least I'm keeping you company.

118
00:05:38,296 --> 00:05:39,297
What?

119
00:05:39,380 --> 00:05:41,591
I don't need a chaperone.

120
00:05:43,551 --> 00:05:46,387
You know, I saw the cap
you left at the court.

121
00:05:47,055 --> 00:05:48,514
That's mine.

122
00:05:48,598 --> 00:05:50,892
It has sentimental value to me.
Give it back!

123
00:05:52,060 --> 00:05:53,186
Really?

124
00:05:54,562 --> 00:05:57,273
I already threw it away. It looked old.

125
00:05:57,356 --> 00:05:58,524
Are you crazy?

126
00:05:59,358 --> 00:06:00,359
Why did you throw it away?

127
00:06:00,443 --> 00:06:01,903
[in English] Relax!

128
00:06:01,986 --> 00:06:03,821
I'll buy you a new one, branded.

129
00:06:03,905 --> 00:06:05,823
You know, I don't care about
those branded things.

130
00:06:05,907 --> 00:06:07,909
I said it's important to me.

131
00:06:08,493 --> 00:06:10,536
[chuckling]

132
00:06:11,120 --> 00:06:12,205
You're laughing?

133
00:06:12,288 --> 00:06:14,415
Relax! Just relax.

134
00:06:14,499 --> 00:06:16,459
Your cap is at home. I'll give it back.

135
00:06:16,542 --> 00:06:17,376
Don't worry.

136
00:06:17,460 --> 00:06:18,961
- Are you crazy?
- Oh!

137
00:06:19,045 --> 00:06:21,380
- [Karla] Are you messing with me?
- [Mongki] Hey!

138
00:06:21,464 --> 00:06:23,674
Why did you push Gavin, huh?

139
00:06:24,634 --> 00:06:26,552
- [exhilarating music playing]
- [laughing]

140
00:06:26,636 --> 00:06:28,721
[in English] You want me
to throw her out too?

141
00:06:29,263 --> 00:06:31,474
[in English] Yes? Yes!

142
00:06:31,557 --> 00:06:33,434
- [laughs]
- [crowd cheering, clapping]

143
00:06:36,104 --> 00:06:37,188
[Vladimir, in English] What the hell?

144
00:06:37,855 --> 00:06:38,815
[in English] Who are you?

145
00:06:39,398 --> 00:06:42,110
[in English] Why don't you pick
on somebody your own size?

146
00:06:44,779 --> 00:06:46,781
- [grunting, groaning]
- [brazen music playing]

147
00:06:47,698 --> 00:06:50,785
[in Russian] I'll kill you right here!

148
00:06:51,369 --> 00:06:53,663
[in Russian] You can try.

149
00:06:53,746 --> 00:06:56,791
[brazen music continues]

150
00:06:58,167 --> 00:06:59,252
[in Russian] You're gonna get it.

151
00:07:00,920 --> 00:07:02,130
[in English] So…

152
00:07:03,005 --> 00:07:05,341
[in English] You are a member
of the human trafficking group,

153
00:07:05,424 --> 00:07:06,592
Black Meridian, eh?

154
00:07:07,969 --> 00:07:10,263
[in English] Get out of my country,
you pig!

155
00:07:13,433 --> 00:07:14,642
- [laughs]
- [crowd cheering]

156
00:07:14,725 --> 00:07:15,893
[in Russian] Let's dance!

157
00:07:16,644 --> 00:07:19,021
[upbeat music playing]

158
00:07:21,732 --> 00:07:23,025
[grunting]

159
00:07:23,109 --> 00:07:25,445
- [smacks]
- [crowd cheering]

160
00:07:26,028 --> 00:07:27,405
Okay.

161
00:07:29,073 --> 00:07:31,117
- [thudding]
- [grunting]

162
00:07:32,869 --> 00:07:35,121
[crowd cheering, clapping]

163
00:07:37,874 --> 00:07:39,250
[grunting]

164
00:07:40,626 --> 00:07:42,753
- [thud]
- [crowd cheering]

165
00:07:47,592 --> 00:07:50,386
[cheering and applauding]

166
00:07:50,470 --> 00:07:52,805
[in English] Hey. What happened here?

167
00:07:52,889 --> 00:07:53,890
Whoo!

168
00:07:54,515 --> 00:07:55,766
[in English] Ah, nothing.

169
00:07:56,434 --> 00:07:57,768
[in English] That old man just hit me.

170
00:07:58,352 --> 00:07:59,645
- [Vladimir chuckles]
- [in English] Let's get him.

171
00:07:59,729 --> 00:08:01,355
[in English] All right, let's go.

172
00:08:01,856 --> 00:08:03,316
[Vladimir chuckles]

173
00:08:03,816 --> 00:08:05,776
[Vladimir chuckles, in English]
Let's find him.

174
00:08:05,860 --> 00:08:08,529
Sir, only gold card members are priority.

175
00:08:08,613 --> 00:08:09,864
I'm a gold card member.

176
00:08:09,947 --> 00:08:12,783
But your companion

177
00:08:12,867 --> 00:08:14,410
tussled with Boss Alpha's referral,

178
00:08:14,494 --> 00:08:15,912
Chipper Arenas.

179
00:08:15,995 --> 00:08:18,122
I'll handle Alpha. Come on.

180
00:08:18,623 --> 00:08:20,583
[Chipper] You're not listening to me.

181
00:08:20,666 --> 00:08:24,295
I am Chipper Arenas,
the friend of Boss Alpha.

182
00:08:24,378 --> 00:08:25,505
That's right, sir.

183
00:08:25,588 --> 00:08:28,508
But you need a gold card to enter.

184
00:08:28,591 --> 00:08:30,051
It's gone.

185
00:08:30,134 --> 00:08:33,095
I almost lost my Rolex here
yesterday, remember?

186
00:08:33,179 --> 00:08:35,765
My gold card was also in that jacket,

187
00:08:35,848 --> 00:08:37,683
so it must have been stolen too!

188
00:08:38,309 --> 00:08:39,185
Here.

189
00:08:40,102 --> 00:08:41,812
Here's my ID.

190
00:08:43,940 --> 00:08:47,193
[inquisitive music playing]

191
00:08:48,945 --> 00:08:49,904
‪[blipping]

192
00:08:51,155 --> 00:08:52,657
Sir, your name is already encoded.

193
00:08:52,740 --> 00:08:55,576
Goddamnit! Eh, then he got in, that thief!

194
00:08:56,160 --> 00:08:57,078
What?

195
00:09:00,248 --> 00:09:01,791
You're too slow.

196
00:09:01,874 --> 00:09:03,709
This is the second time
I've been inconvenienced!

197
00:09:03,793 --> 00:09:05,628
I already sent someone, sir.

198
00:09:06,212 --> 00:09:07,171
- Move aside!
- Sir, sir, sir!

199
00:09:07,255 --> 00:09:08,631
- I'll tell Boss Alpha to fire you!
- Sir…

200
00:09:09,882 --> 00:09:10,925
- Darryl…
- [gasping]

201
00:09:11,008 --> 00:09:13,844
You should have been rushed
to the hospital already!

202
00:09:13,928 --> 00:09:16,305
- Let's help him.
- [muttering]

203
00:09:17,265 --> 00:09:18,266
Darryl…

204
00:09:19,267 --> 00:09:21,102
Do we still have hope?

205
00:09:21,686 --> 00:09:23,020
This is my fault.

206
00:09:23,604 --> 00:09:25,356
If it weren't for me,

207
00:09:25,439 --> 00:09:27,942
you could have left this hell
of a place the other day.

208
00:09:28,985 --> 00:09:31,904
Darryl, remember the guy I told you about?

209
00:09:31,988 --> 00:09:35,408
He's here. He'll help us escape.

210
00:09:35,491 --> 00:09:37,076
Be strong, okay?

211
00:09:37,994 --> 00:09:39,287
[gasping] He's alone.

212
00:09:40,621 --> 00:09:41,998
I don't know…

213
00:09:42,081 --> 00:09:43,833
how he'll manage…

214
00:09:43,916 --> 00:09:45,167
to save us.

215
00:09:46,919 --> 00:09:49,922
I don't want
to hold out hope anymore, Ame.

216
00:09:50,006 --> 00:09:51,549
Ouch! Ouch!

217
00:09:52,133 --> 00:09:54,885
- Darryl! Darryl!
- Ouch! Ouch! [shouts]

218
00:09:54,969 --> 00:09:57,430
- Darryl, what's happening? Darryl!
- [pained shouting]

219
00:09:57,513 --> 00:09:58,806
Darryl!

220
00:09:58,889 --> 00:10:00,057
Let's ask for help!

221
00:10:00,141 --> 00:10:01,892
Help! Help!

222
00:10:01,976 --> 00:10:04,270
Help! Help us!

223
00:10:04,353 --> 00:10:07,106
[crowd pleading] Help!

224
00:10:07,189 --> 00:10:08,482
Darryl!

225
00:10:08,566 --> 00:10:12,236
- Help! Help! Call them!
- [crowd shouting]

226
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:14,655
Darryl! Darryl!

227
00:10:15,281 --> 00:10:16,115
Darryl!

228
00:10:16,198 --> 00:10:17,742
Ask for help!

229
00:10:17,825 --> 00:10:19,076
Help!

230
00:10:19,160 --> 00:10:22,079
- [crowd pleading]
- [Ame] Darryl.

231
00:10:22,163 --> 00:10:23,789
Darryl, be strong!

232
00:10:23,873 --> 00:10:27,126
You still need to see your father.
Your father is waiting for you.

233
00:10:27,209 --> 00:10:28,836
Help! Help!

234
00:10:28,919 --> 00:10:32,089
[crowd pleading]

235
00:10:34,550 --> 00:10:37,053
Sir, where are you going?
Customers are not allowed inside.

236
00:10:38,220 --> 00:10:39,430
Ah…

237
00:10:40,306 --> 00:10:42,975
[in English] Ah… I'm sorry,
I'm sorry. I, ah…

238
00:10:43,059 --> 00:10:44,518
[in English] I just wanna…

239
00:10:44,602 --> 00:10:46,771
wanna see one of the fighters.

240
00:10:46,854 --> 00:10:49,231
It's… Ame, Ame.

241
00:10:49,315 --> 00:10:51,192
- [English] You know, I… really like her.
- Uh…

242
00:10:51,275 --> 00:10:54,236
Sir, just wait outside.
I'll call the stage manager.

243
00:10:56,030 --> 00:10:58,866
Lito. Check all members inside.

244
00:10:58,949 --> 00:11:01,285
Someone is using Chipper Arenas's card.

245
00:11:01,369 --> 00:11:02,370
Okay, sir.

246
00:11:05,581 --> 00:11:07,958
[inquisitive music continues]

247
00:11:09,418 --> 00:11:12,254
Sir, may I see your gold card?

248
00:11:12,338 --> 00:11:13,672
[in English] Gold card…

249
00:11:13,756 --> 00:11:15,216
Who are you?

250
00:11:15,299 --> 00:11:16,967
- Let go of me!
- Brother…

251
00:11:17,051 --> 00:11:19,470
You pushed my boss's son!

252
00:11:19,553 --> 00:11:20,805
So, you're a nanny?

253
00:11:22,181 --> 00:11:24,225
You're a grownup, you still need a nanny?

254
00:11:24,308 --> 00:11:25,518
He's not my nanny.

255
00:11:26,185 --> 00:11:27,311
Bro Mongki, let go of her!

256
00:11:27,395 --> 00:11:28,312
[in English] She's with me!

257
00:11:28,396 --> 00:11:29,647
But…

258
00:11:29,730 --> 00:11:30,564
[in English] Let her go!

259
00:11:30,648 --> 00:11:31,982
She's with me.

260
00:11:34,819 --> 00:11:36,695
You're lucky. You're lucky.

261
00:11:38,197 --> 00:11:39,365
I'm sorry, okay?

262
00:11:39,448 --> 00:11:41,075
I'll return your cap tomorrow.

263
00:11:41,158 --> 00:11:43,327
- Let's go!
- Make sure, okay?

264
00:11:45,037 --> 00:11:47,331
I know I've seen that face before.

265
00:11:47,832 --> 00:11:49,917
I'm only looking for one person here!

266
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:50,876
Atoy!

267
00:11:50,960 --> 00:11:53,254
So, if you don't want to get implicated,

268
00:11:53,337 --> 00:11:54,672
just answer me!

269
00:11:54,755 --> 00:11:55,881
[stirring music playing]

270
00:11:55,965 --> 00:11:57,341
Brother Atoy is in trouble.

271
00:11:58,092 --> 00:11:59,427
[line ringing]

272
00:12:00,386 --> 00:12:01,720
For verification only, sir.

273
00:12:01,804 --> 00:12:03,806
[Atoy, in English] Gold card,
of course, of course.

274
00:12:03,889 --> 00:12:06,350
[in English] Understood.
[chuckles] There you go.

275
00:12:06,434 --> 00:12:07,393
‪[machine buzzes]

276
00:12:07,476 --> 00:12:08,436
[in English] Gold card.

277
00:12:12,898 --> 00:12:14,942
Sir, don't cover it, sir. I can't scan it.

278
00:12:15,985 --> 00:12:17,319
Okay?

279
00:12:17,403 --> 00:12:18,779
[in English] Oh, oh my--

280
00:12:19,947 --> 00:12:21,532
- [thuds]
- [groaning]

281
00:12:21,615 --> 00:12:24,160
[in English] Oh, I'm…
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

282
00:12:24,243 --> 00:12:26,287
It's your fault. You kept blocking me.

283
00:12:26,370 --> 00:12:29,206
- Oh no, you're bleeding. I'm so sorry.
- [gasps] You're doing this on purpose!

284
00:12:29,290 --> 00:12:30,583
[in English] I'm so sorry.
Can I see? Can I see?

285
00:12:30,666 --> 00:12:32,501
[in English] Up, up, up, up.
Can I see? Can I see?

286
00:12:32,585 --> 00:12:35,129
[in English] Oh, oh, that's so bad.
I'm sorry, sorry.

287
00:12:35,212 --> 00:12:38,007
[grunting and groaning]

288
00:12:38,090 --> 00:12:40,342
[brazen music playing]

289
00:12:40,426 --> 00:12:43,179
[crowd shouting]

290
00:12:43,262 --> 00:12:44,597
Son of a…

291
00:12:44,680 --> 00:12:46,891
Shut up! Be quiet!

292
00:12:46,974 --> 00:12:48,517
Help us!

293
00:12:48,601 --> 00:12:50,936
We need to bring
our friend to the hospital!

294
00:12:51,020 --> 00:12:52,521
Leave him!

295
00:12:52,605 --> 00:12:54,148
- He's going to die anyway!
- [Tessie gasps]

296
00:12:54,231 --> 00:12:56,609
You're so cruel! Don't you have a heart?

297
00:12:56,692 --> 00:12:58,194
We're humans too!

298
00:12:58,277 --> 00:12:59,361
Son of…

299
00:12:59,445 --> 00:13:00,738
What's your problem, huh?

300
00:13:00,821 --> 00:13:02,490
- Huh? What's your problem?
- [thuds]

301
00:13:02,573 --> 00:13:03,741
Stop it!

302
00:13:04,700 --> 00:13:07,244
What do you think we are? Toys?

303
00:13:07,328 --> 00:13:09,163
[Tessie sobbing]

304
00:13:13,584 --> 00:13:15,503
Ame… He's gone…

305
00:13:16,086 --> 00:13:17,755
Darryl is gone.

306
00:13:17,838 --> 00:13:19,423
- What?
- [man] He's gone.

307
00:13:20,508 --> 00:13:23,427
- No… Darryl, Darryl, wake up!
- [tense music playing]

308
00:13:23,511 --> 00:13:25,638
Darryl, your father is waiting for you!

309
00:13:25,721 --> 00:13:27,598
We're still leaving this place!

310
00:13:28,724 --> 00:13:30,059
Darryl!

311
00:13:30,142 --> 00:13:32,937
Darryl, wake up!

312
00:13:33,020 --> 00:13:36,273
Didn't you say
you'd go back to your father?

313
00:13:37,316 --> 00:13:40,694
Darryl! Darryl, wake up!

314
00:13:40,778 --> 00:13:42,988
[sobbing] Darryl!

315
00:13:43,072 --> 00:13:46,116
This is the fault of that evil customer!

316
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:48,285
He toyed with Darryl!

317
00:13:48,369 --> 00:13:49,912
He killed Darryl!

318
00:13:49,995 --> 00:13:52,414
[sobbing]

319
00:13:52,498 --> 00:13:54,625
Let's avenge Darryl!

320
00:13:54,708 --> 00:13:57,044
[uneasy music playing]

321
00:13:57,127 --> 00:13:58,671
Attack!

322
00:13:58,754 --> 00:14:00,714
What? Ouch! Ouch!

323
00:14:00,798 --> 00:14:04,176
Ouch! Wait! What?

324
00:14:04,260 --> 00:14:06,428
Ouch! Ouch! What?

325
00:14:07,972 --> 00:14:08,806
Ouch!

326
00:14:08,889 --> 00:14:11,475
- Hurry! Hurry!
- [energetic club music playing]

327
00:14:11,559 --> 00:14:14,311
Did you see an old man?

328
00:14:14,395 --> 00:14:16,897
He was beating up my friend. Chi-- What?

329
00:14:16,981 --> 00:14:18,649
Chipper Arenas.

330
00:14:18,732 --> 00:14:20,943
That's him over there, sir.
That's Chipper Arenas.

331
00:14:22,778 --> 00:14:24,238
[in English] That's not him.

332
00:14:24,321 --> 00:14:26,282
[in English] He's not even wearing
the same clothes.

333
00:14:26,866 --> 00:14:28,576
What? Are you sure?

334
00:14:29,076 --> 00:14:31,912
He was complaining that someone
was using his gold card.

335
00:14:32,997 --> 00:14:34,039
[Vladimir, in English] What is he saying?

336
00:14:34,123 --> 00:14:37,293
[tense music playing]

337
00:14:37,376 --> 00:14:40,004
[in English] The person
we're looking for is an imposter.

338
00:14:40,087 --> 00:14:41,255
Find him.

339
00:14:42,339 --> 00:14:43,549
[in English] He looks old,

340
00:14:43,632 --> 00:14:45,718
but he was pretty quick
on his feet, I must say.

341
00:14:45,801 --> 00:14:47,261
- [in English] Old?
- [in English] Old.

342
00:14:49,430 --> 00:14:52,391
Sir! Your gold card, sir.

343
00:14:54,059 --> 00:14:55,978
- [thuds]
- [groans]

344
00:14:58,272 --> 00:15:02,443
Sir… I'll just scan it… [groans]

345
00:15:03,819 --> 00:15:06,155
- [thudding]
- [groaning]

346
00:15:13,162 --> 00:15:14,747
[in English] There's the pesky old man.

347
00:15:15,247 --> 00:15:18,959
[tense music playing]

348
00:15:20,210 --> 00:15:23,088
- Security, proceed to the hallway.
- [in English] Copy.

349
00:15:23,672 --> 00:15:27,343
[tense music continues]

350
00:15:31,513 --> 00:15:32,681
Wait.

351
00:15:32,765 --> 00:15:33,891
Where are you going?

352
00:15:33,974 --> 00:15:35,976
Where else can I go?

353
00:15:36,060 --> 00:15:38,604
If you want to enter, you must pay first.

354
00:15:39,480 --> 00:15:40,522
Ah…

355
00:15:41,523 --> 00:15:43,609
I'm just here to fetch my boss.

356
00:15:43,692 --> 00:15:46,320
His wife is looking for him.
He's not answering.

357
00:15:46,403 --> 00:15:48,614
Your style is lousy.
You want to get in for free?

358
00:15:49,198 --> 00:15:50,658
Free?

359
00:15:50,741 --> 00:15:53,744
Bro, I'm a woman!
That's only for dirty old men!

360
00:15:54,495 --> 00:15:56,372
I don't know what your preference is.

361
00:15:56,455 --> 00:15:59,041
But if you want to enter,
you must pay first.

362
00:15:59,124 --> 00:16:01,043
[curious music playing]

363
00:16:01,126 --> 00:16:02,252
Oh…

364
00:16:03,253 --> 00:16:04,296
[in English] You wanna go inside?

365
00:16:04,964 --> 00:16:06,757
I just need to find my boss.

366
00:16:09,718 --> 00:16:12,054
[in English] Boss, she's with me.

367
00:16:13,097 --> 00:16:15,057
Come on. Let's go find your boss.

368
00:16:19,728 --> 00:16:21,355
[intense music playing]

369
00:16:21,438 --> 00:16:24,441
[grunting and groaning]

370
00:16:25,192 --> 00:16:27,027
[whacks]

371
00:16:30,864 --> 00:16:31,782
[in English] Where's your boss?

372
00:16:31,865 --> 00:16:33,867
He's not here.
As far as I know, he went to the VIP.

373
00:16:33,951 --> 00:16:35,744
VIP? This way.

374
00:16:36,578 --> 00:16:37,663
[gunshot]

375
00:16:37,746 --> 00:16:40,708
[electricity crackling]

376
00:16:41,417 --> 00:16:42,710
- [whoosh]
- [thud]

377
00:16:44,003 --> 00:16:47,172
[electricity crackling]

378
00:16:47,256 --> 00:16:48,215
[crowd screaming]

379
00:16:48,298 --> 00:16:51,969
- [alarm ringing]
- [crowd clamoring]

380
00:16:53,012 --> 00:16:53,887
Someone's shooting?

381
00:16:53,971 --> 00:16:54,805
‪[gasps]

382
00:16:54,888 --> 00:16:56,056
[Karla] What's that?

383
00:16:56,140 --> 00:16:59,184
- [crowd clamoring]
- [alarm ringing]

384
00:17:00,269 --> 00:17:01,103
‪[indistinct shouting]

385
00:17:06,442 --> 00:17:07,776
What's happening?

386
00:17:08,485 --> 00:17:11,488
They said they're trying to catch
a gold star member imposter.

387
00:17:12,740 --> 00:17:14,491
[Mongki] Let's get out of here, Gavin.
It's dangerous!

388
00:17:14,575 --> 00:17:16,368
- Brother Atoy…
- [Gavin, in English] What about Dad?

389
00:17:16,452 --> 00:17:17,870
[Mongki] Your dad can handle himself.

390
00:17:17,953 --> 00:17:19,872
He'll be angrier
if something bad happens to you.

391
00:17:19,955 --> 00:17:20,956
[in English] Please go help him!

392
00:17:21,040 --> 00:17:22,291
- I can go home alone!
- No!

393
00:17:22,374 --> 00:17:24,460
No! I'll go back for your dad.

394
00:17:24,543 --> 00:17:26,378
What's important is I get you out first.

395
00:17:26,962 --> 00:17:28,255
- Let's go!
- Okay, okay!

396
00:17:28,839 --> 00:17:30,674
- [in English] Let's go.
- [in English] Hey, we need to go.

397
00:17:32,843 --> 00:17:34,219
Where did she go?

398
00:17:34,303 --> 00:17:37,222
[suspenseful music playing]

399
00:17:39,725 --> 00:17:43,020
[electricity crackling]

400
00:17:43,520 --> 00:17:45,230
[grunting]

401
00:17:45,314 --> 00:17:46,440
[thud]

402
00:17:46,523 --> 00:17:47,816
[crashes]

403
00:17:47,900 --> 00:17:49,943
[tense dramatic music playing]

404
00:17:51,612 --> 00:17:53,030
[grunting]

405
00:17:53,947 --> 00:17:56,700
- [thudding]
- [grunting]

406
00:17:59,787 --> 00:18:00,788
Old man…

407
00:18:02,456 --> 00:18:03,749
It's my turn.

408
00:18:04,249 --> 00:18:06,126
[chuckles, in English] My dear…

409
00:18:07,503 --> 00:18:11,423
Didn't your parents
teach you to respect your elders?

410
00:18:12,633 --> 00:18:14,635
After I'm done with you, you'll be wiser.

411
00:18:17,554 --> 00:18:18,972
That's a promise, huh?

412
00:18:19,598 --> 00:18:21,725
[brazen music continues]

413
00:18:21,809 --> 00:18:24,186
[in English] Go get your prize. Get it.

414
00:18:24,269 --> 00:18:26,605
- [in English] You sure?
- [in English] Yes.

415
00:18:28,065 --> 00:18:29,066
[Vladimir, in English] Okay.

416
00:18:30,192 --> 00:18:31,860
[grunting and groaning]

417
00:18:32,694 --> 00:18:33,821
[in English] Good luck!

418
00:18:33,904 --> 00:18:35,781
[grunting and groaning]

419
00:18:41,995 --> 00:18:44,498
I thought you were going to hit me?

420
00:18:44,581 --> 00:18:47,709
[scoffs] "Win-sure, win-sure," jerk.

421
00:18:47,793 --> 00:18:49,795
[tense music continues]

422
00:18:55,134 --> 00:18:56,176
[music fades]

423
00:18:56,260 --> 00:18:57,386
[in English] There she is.

424
00:18:58,345 --> 00:19:00,514
- [Ame] What are you doing? Let go of me!
- [Vladimir grunts]

425
00:19:00,597 --> 00:19:03,684
[Ame] Let go of me!

426
00:19:11,024 --> 00:19:12,484
- [sinister music playing]
- [alarm ringing]

427
00:19:12,568 --> 00:19:17,573
[electricity crackling]

428
00:19:19,616 --> 00:19:20,701
- You're dead now!
- [gun firing]

429
00:19:22,119 --> 00:19:24,204
- [gun firing]
- [Red grunts]

430
00:19:24,288 --> 00:19:25,247
Stop it!

431
00:19:25,330 --> 00:19:27,416
[tense music continues]

432
00:19:31,587 --> 00:19:34,673
- [clamoring]
- [man] Stop it!

433
00:19:34,756 --> 00:19:36,842
You're being stubborn, huh! Move aside!

434
00:19:36,925 --> 00:19:39,136
[clamoring]

435
00:19:39,219 --> 00:19:41,597
Stop it! Don't be stubborn, huh!

436
00:19:41,680 --> 00:19:44,558
[clamoring]

437
00:19:44,641 --> 00:19:45,601
Ouch! Stop it!

438
00:19:45,684 --> 00:19:47,394
- You're so annoying!
- [groans]

439
00:19:47,477 --> 00:19:48,854
- Punch him!
- Ouch!

440
00:19:48,937 --> 00:19:51,523
What the hell? Ouch!

441
00:19:51,607 --> 00:19:53,025
You're all stubborn!

442
00:19:53,108 --> 00:19:54,067
Get out of here!

443
00:19:54,151 --> 00:19:56,069
- [thud]
- Oh! Ouch!

444
00:19:56,153 --> 00:19:58,780
- [thudding]
- [grunting]

445
00:20:01,116 --> 00:20:02,284
That's enough.

446
00:20:03,368 --> 00:20:04,453
Ame!

447
00:20:05,287 --> 00:20:06,997
- Where's Ame?
- Ame is gone.

448
00:20:08,207 --> 00:20:11,251
Are you the guy she said would help her?

449
00:20:12,252 --> 00:20:13,670
Yes, where is she?

450
00:20:13,754 --> 00:20:17,090
The Russian took her.
He's probably bringing her to Japan.

451
00:20:24,014 --> 00:20:25,057
[Red coughs]

452
00:20:26,391 --> 00:20:27,768
Boss, are you okay?

453
00:20:27,851 --> 00:20:29,102
[coughs] Do I look okay?

454
00:20:29,186 --> 00:20:30,729
That imposter fooled me!

455
00:20:31,480 --> 00:20:32,356
Let's find him.

456
00:20:32,439 --> 00:20:34,149
Boss, where are you going? Let's go!

457
00:20:34,233 --> 00:20:35,943
- We might get trapped in this fire.
- No!

458
00:20:36,026 --> 00:20:36,944
I need to outsmart him!

459
00:20:37,027 --> 00:20:38,987
[Tessie] That's the customer
who killed Darryl!

460
00:20:39,071 --> 00:20:40,155
Let's avenge Darryl!

461
00:20:40,239 --> 00:20:41,448
[man] For Darryl!

462
00:20:41,531 --> 00:20:42,908
[grunting and groaning]

463
00:20:42,991 --> 00:20:45,494
[grunting]

464
00:20:46,495 --> 00:20:48,830
Ame? Ame!

465
00:20:48,914 --> 00:20:51,124
[tense music playing]

466
00:20:53,252 --> 00:20:54,795
[line ringing]

467
00:20:56,088 --> 00:20:58,590
[phone ringing]

468
00:20:58,674 --> 00:21:01,385
Brother Atoy! I've been calling you.

469
00:21:01,468 --> 00:21:03,512
The one who was looking
for you before is inside.

470
00:21:03,595 --> 00:21:06,765
I got out through the back.
Bring the car here, quick.

471
00:21:06,848 --> 00:21:08,809
What's happening? Why was there shooting?

472
00:21:09,393 --> 00:21:11,853
Never mind! They took Ame.

473
00:21:12,437 --> 00:21:14,773
Hurry, we might not catch up.

474
00:21:14,856 --> 00:21:17,943
[brazen music playing]

475
00:21:20,028 --> 00:21:22,155
Ame! Ame!

476
00:21:22,239 --> 00:21:25,325
[exhilarating music playing]

477
00:21:31,581 --> 00:21:32,874
Where's my key?

478
00:21:33,458 --> 00:21:34,918
My key! [sharp inhale]

479
00:21:35,002 --> 00:21:37,254
[uneasy music playing]

480
00:21:48,932 --> 00:21:51,018
- Ame!
- [whining]

481
00:21:51,101 --> 00:21:53,854
- [Atoy] Ame! Ame!
- That's Big Brother.

482
00:21:53,937 --> 00:21:55,314
- [Atoy] Ame!
- Brother!

483
00:21:55,397 --> 00:21:56,565
- [shrieks]
- [gasps]

484
00:21:57,190 --> 00:21:58,066
- [shrieking]
- Ouch!

485
00:21:58,984 --> 00:22:01,153
- [Ame] Brother!
- Ame!

486
00:22:02,029 --> 00:22:05,240
- [in Russian] I'll kill you here.
- You can try.

487
00:22:06,575 --> 00:22:07,784
- [whistles]
- [exhilarating music playing]

488
00:22:07,868 --> 00:22:09,494
[in Russian] You're gonna get it.

489
00:22:10,162 --> 00:22:12,456
[in Russian] Let's dance.

490
00:22:12,539 --> 00:22:15,167
[exhilarating music playing]

491
00:22:18,337 --> 00:22:19,463
What are you doing?

492
00:22:19,546 --> 00:22:21,131
Can't you wait?

493
00:22:24,217 --> 00:22:25,552
[in English] Are you looking for this?

494
00:22:27,345 --> 00:22:28,513
Why do you have my key?

495
00:22:28,597 --> 00:22:31,391
I saw it inside. It must have fallen
when you suddenly left.

496
00:22:36,063 --> 00:22:37,105
What are you doing here?

497
00:22:37,189 --> 00:22:38,065
[in English] Can I hitch a ride?

498
00:22:38,148 --> 00:22:39,900
My companions left me.

499
00:22:39,983 --> 00:22:41,568
Ride with someone else.

500
00:22:41,651 --> 00:22:43,487
Don't you see I'm in a hurry?

501
00:22:43,570 --> 00:22:45,280
And my boss will scold me!

502
00:22:45,363 --> 00:22:46,615
[in English] Hey, you owe me.

503
00:22:46,698 --> 00:22:48,366
I'll just ride with you
up to the main road anyway.

504
00:22:48,450 --> 00:22:50,952
[sharp inhale] Do what you want.

505
00:22:52,037 --> 00:22:55,207
[stirring music playing]

506
00:22:55,874 --> 00:22:58,460
Let go of me! Let…

507
00:22:58,543 --> 00:23:00,754
Let go of me!

508
00:23:00,837 --> 00:23:03,965
Brother! Brother! Brother!

509
00:23:04,049 --> 00:23:06,009
- Let go of me!
- [Vladimir, in English] Don't worry!

510
00:23:06,093 --> 00:23:07,219
[Ame] Help! Help me!

511
00:23:07,302 --> 00:23:09,304
Help! Help!

512
00:23:09,387 --> 00:23:10,514
[grunts]

513
00:23:10,597 --> 00:23:11,640
[Ame] Brother, Brother, help!

514
00:23:11,723 --> 00:23:12,974
- Help, Brother!
- [Vladimir, in English] Come here.

515
00:23:13,058 --> 00:23:14,518
[Ame] Brother! Brother help!

516
00:23:14,601 --> 00:23:15,977
Let go of me!

517
00:23:16,061 --> 00:23:17,312
Brother, help!

518
00:23:17,395 --> 00:23:18,605
[in Russian] Goodbye!

519
00:23:18,688 --> 00:23:19,648
Brother, help!

520
00:23:19,731 --> 00:23:21,525
Help!

521
00:23:21,608 --> 00:23:25,070
[uneasy music playing]

522
00:23:34,329 --> 00:23:35,622
Come on, come on, let's go!

523
00:23:36,665 --> 00:23:38,750
- Who's this?
- Later, Brother! Let's go!

524
00:23:38,834 --> 00:23:41,211
- [gasps]
- [exhilarating music playing]

525
00:23:43,588 --> 00:23:44,965
Let's go! Let's go! Let's go!

526
00:23:47,592 --> 00:23:50,595
- [intense music playing]
- [blipping]

527
00:23:54,516 --> 00:23:56,309
[man] It's collection day today.

528
00:23:56,393 --> 00:23:58,353
I just gave money two weeks ago, guys.

529
00:23:58,436 --> 00:23:59,771
- [man] You really don't want to?
- [grunts]

530
00:23:59,855 --> 00:24:01,481
- [screams]
- Let's hurt him a little more.

531
00:24:01,565 --> 00:24:03,567
- Let's add…
- [screams]

532
00:24:03,650 --> 00:24:06,069
[Tonet] <i>Atoy has another job</i>
<i>besides tailoring.</i>

533
00:24:06,153 --> 00:24:08,697
<i>Only Karla and I know that.</i>

534
00:24:08,780 --> 00:24:10,657
<i>Atoy's job is hard.</i>

535
00:24:10,740 --> 00:24:12,576
It's risky if other people find out.

536
00:24:12,659 --> 00:24:14,119
So, what is he? Military?

537
00:24:14,202 --> 00:24:17,789
That's what I tell my people. I need
to know who he's connected to.

538
00:24:17,873 --> 00:24:20,167
[Red] <i>So I can prepare</i>
<i>for our confrontation.</i>

539
00:24:20,250 --> 00:24:22,502
‪UP NEXT

540
00:24:25,881 --> 00:24:28,216
Subtitle translation by: Rachel C. Arias
